.SH NAME
Selection.selectAllChildren \- Selection: selectAllChildren() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]Selection.selectAllChildren()\f[B]\f[R] method adds all
the children of the specified node to the selection.
Previous selection is lost.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
selectAllChildren(parentNode)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]parentNode\f[R]
All children of \f[CR]parentNode\f[R] will be selected.
\f[CR]parentNode\f[R] itself is not part of the selection.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
